depositToken(address,address,uint256).details: This is mainly used for boosting balancer LP tokens
depositToken(address,address,uint256).notice: Allows the owner to deposit tokens

exitLock().notice: Exit the veToken lock. For this function to be called and not revert, tokens had to be locked previously, and the contract must have been paused for lockDuration in order to prevent lock extensions by calling lock(). This function will recover tokens on the contract, which can then be moved by calling withdraw() as a PCVController if the contract is also a PCVDeposit, for instance.

gaugeController().notice: address of the gauge controller used for voting

lock().notice: Deposit tokens to get veTokens. Set lock duration to lockDuration. The only way to withdraw tokens will be to pause this contract for lockDuration and then call exitLock().

managerContract().notice: manager contract used to manage BPT token deposits
